WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.634
ALL FIGURES, INCIDENTS,
LOCATIONS, ORGANIZATIONS,

00:51.718 --> 00:52.552
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

00:52.635 --> 00:53.762
CHILD ACTORS
AND ANIMALS WERE FILMED

00:53.845 --> 00:54.971
SAFELY IN ACCORDANCE
WITH GUIDELINES.

00:56.056 --> 01:00.060
Could one of these talismans
be my husband's?

01:01.561 --> 01:06.107
Perhaps, but you should not
be too quick to touch it.

01:06.775 --> 01:10.945
We don't know how your son
is connected to the talismans yet.

01:11.821 --> 01:13.907
Oh, right.

01:17.869 --> 01:19.037
Anyway,

01:19.120 --> 01:22.832
what is it that you want to find here?

01:22.916 --> 01:27.086
I-rang told me something before.

01:27.170 --> 01:29.297
How did you come to see that ghost?

01:30.465 --> 01:33.301
There was a desk
that used to belong to the shaman.

01:33.384 --> 01:36.012
I found an old incense burner
in the drawer.

01:36.095 --> 01:38.723
That incense burner seems to be the cause.

01:40.850 --> 01:41.976
But I can't find it.

01:49.150 --> 01:50.485
Then, what?

01:51.903 --> 01:55.949
I better look for the male shaman
who used to summon spirits here.

02:15.927 --> 02:16.928
Let me.

02:27.981 --> 02:29.607
I can do it myself.

02:29.691 --> 02:31.568
It's better to be safe than sorry.

02:32.777 --> 02:33.736
Sorry?

02:34.320 --> 02:35.697
You could say otherwise later.

02:37.240 --> 02:39.242
I'm not like that.

02:39.325 --> 02:41.369
It doesn't matter what you're like.

02:41.911 --> 02:43.580
It's just that I don't trust people.

02:44.330 --> 02:47.500
Why? Why don't you trust people?

02:49.127 --> 02:50.628
It was dangerous back there.

02:51.212 --> 02:52.630
The cross light was red.

02:53.798 --> 02:54.924
Oh, that.

02:59.679 --> 03:01.472
I go out of control from time to time.

03:04.142 --> 03:06.603
What were you doing here?

03:07.729 --> 03:10.023
Glory Entertainment is my new client.

03:10.899 --> 03:11.983
What about you?

03:12.525 --> 03:14.235
Are you hired for a case or something?

03:14.319 --> 03:16.112
No, that's not it.

03:17.614 --> 03:19.282
It's an entertainment agency, you know.

03:20.033 --> 03:21.159
Where artists are.

03:22.035 --> 03:23.578
I was there to see my favorite artist.

03:26.164 --> 03:27.832
- What?
- An idol.

03:33.588 --> 03:34.589
That's on nice and snug.

03:40.386 --> 03:42.430
Was he serious or joking?

03:43.431 --> 03:44.766
He certainly is an oddball.

04:14.587 --> 04:16.589
Who was that woman earlier?

04:18.341 --> 04:20.510
Oh, she's an attorney.

04:20.593 --> 04:22.762
She defended the other side
during my previous case.

04:24.639 --> 04:25.890
Do you have a crush on her?

04:25.974 --> 04:28.226
Are you interested
when you shouldn't be into her?

04:29.352 --> 04:30.186
What are you saying?

04:30.270 --> 04:33.106
Your face was super red like an apple.

04:33.189 --> 04:35.358
That was because I was possessed!

04:41.990 --> 04:43.574
I'm not angry.

04:43.658 --> 04:44.826
I know.

04:48.162 --> 04:49.497
I'm just sorry.

04:50.790 --> 04:52.709
You almost got into an accident
because of me.

04:54.127 --> 04:57.213
I didn't, so it's okay.

04:59.007 --> 05:01.676
Anyway, why did you
run after Ko Jong-seok?

05:02.552 --> 05:06.764
His ringtone was
the one I heard when I died.

05:08.558 --> 05:09.392
What?

05:14.856 --> 05:15.857
Excuse me.

05:15.940 --> 05:16.941
Who are you?

05:17.025 --> 05:19.068
I'm an attorney
working for Glory Entertainment.

05:19.610 --> 05:22.155
Could I check the footage
of the security camera in the hallway?

05:22.238 --> 05:25.950
Nice timing. I was meaning
to call the police anyway.

05:26.576 --> 05:28.828
- The police?
- You say you're an attorney.

05:28.911 --> 05:32.040
Isn't this why you're here?

05:35.084 --> 05:37.086
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

05:41.799 --> 05:43.384
Why are you taking that?

05:43.468 --> 05:46.804
Luckily, this truck
was parked by the road.

05:47.388 --> 05:48.890
Something must've been captured.

05:51.309 --> 05:52.560
Da-bong!

05:52.643 --> 05:54.937
- Welcome home.
- Uncle!

05:55.021 --> 05:56.731
It's so nice to see you.

05:57.356 --> 05:59.650
- Did you have a good day?
- Yes.

06:02.070 --> 06:04.947
Uncle, what happened to your hand?
Did you get hurt?

06:06.657 --> 06:08.034
I-rang.

06:08.117 --> 06:09.702
Did you hurt your hand?

06:09.786 --> 06:13.039
What? Who got hurt? I-rang?

06:13.122 --> 06:14.624
No, it's nothing.

06:15.166 --> 06:18.377
Yes, it's something.
Look. It's wrapped in a bandage.

06:18.461 --> 06:21.339
It's a slight scratch. I'm okay.

06:22.298 --> 06:24.133
- I'm really okay.
- But…

06:24.217 --> 06:26.135
I-rang, let me see your hand.

06:26.219 --> 06:27.220
Goodness.

06:27.970 --> 06:28.846
Geez…

06:35.478 --> 06:37.480
Mother.

06:37.563 --> 06:39.857
What is it? Do we have a large party?

06:39.941 --> 06:41.984
No. I-rang got hurt.

06:42.068 --> 06:43.402
Got hurt?

06:44.070 --> 06:45.113
I was too complacent.

06:45.196 --> 06:47.031
Mother, relax. Calm down.

06:47.615 --> 06:49.951
I'm only letting you know
in case you're curious.

06:50.034 --> 06:51.577
It's not a serious injury.

06:52.245 --> 06:54.330
I'll look into what happened.

06:55.915 --> 06:57.291
Okay.

06:57.875 --> 07:00.336
It may be related to the ghost,

07:00.419 --> 07:01.921
so go and watch him closely.

07:02.004 --> 07:03.339
Yes, Mother.

07:03.422 --> 07:04.757
A ghost?

07:05.550 --> 07:06.717
Well…

07:06.801 --> 07:09.887
Customers love our new dish?

07:10.555 --> 07:11.806
Yes, Mother.

07:11.889 --> 07:14.809
They're obsessed with our new dish
like ghosts. They love it.

07:16.727 --> 07:18.312
What are you two playing at?

07:29.449 --> 07:30.950
STORAGE DEVICE

07:32.577 --> 07:33.744
I-rang.

07:33.828 --> 07:35.788
What happened? Did something happen?

07:35.872 --> 07:37.790
Well, it's nothing.

07:37.874 --> 07:39.000
But…

07:39.584 --> 07:40.960
- One moment.
- Okay.

07:43.004 --> 07:44.005
It starts from here.

07:57.393 --> 07:58.269
What is he doing?

08:00.438 --> 08:03.691
Isn't that the attorney from Taebaek?

08:04.358 --> 08:05.985
Yes, it's Attorney Han.

08:06.068 --> 08:07.445
Right, Attorney Han.

08:14.744 --> 08:15.578
Him…

08:15.661 --> 08:17.497
I told you. He's the vocal trainer.

08:22.793 --> 08:24.962
It looks like
Attorney Han was going after him.

08:30.092 --> 08:31.302
Wait, what?

08:31.385 --> 08:33.471
You were going after him too.

08:33.554 --> 08:34.847
But,

08:34.931 --> 08:37.808
that… wasn't me.

08:44.232 --> 08:45.983
Are we with her?

08:55.368 --> 08:56.452
Hello.

09:02.833 --> 09:04.126
What a nutjob.

09:04.210 --> 09:05.127
I know, right?

09:05.628 --> 09:07.588
Is this enough to find that lunatic?

09:07.672 --> 09:09.006
What?

09:11.509 --> 09:12.468
Yes.

09:14.345 --> 09:15.346
Excuse me for a moment.

09:22.603 --> 09:23.813
<i>Hi, Na-hyun.</i>

09:23.896 --> 09:26.732
When you arrested Cho Gi-cheol,
Attorney Shin I-rang was there, right?

09:27.650 --> 09:28.526
Yes, he was.

09:28.609 --> 09:30.736
Did you interview him as a witness?

09:30.820 --> 09:31.737
<i>Yes, I did.</i>

09:32.363 --> 09:33.906
How did he know about that place?

09:34.490 --> 09:36.409
I asked him the same question,

09:36.492 --> 09:38.828
and he said he got the info
from an unidentified source.

09:39.412 --> 09:40.997
- A source?
<i>- Yes.</i>

09:41.080 --> 09:43.416
He didn't tell me who until the end.

09:43.499 --> 09:46.377
I couldn't question him more
because he helped our investigation.

09:46.460 --> 09:47.878
<i>But why do you ask?</i>

09:47.962 --> 09:50.131
It's nothing. I gotta go.

09:55.261 --> 09:56.429
Wait!

09:57.930 --> 09:58.848
Attorney Shin?

10:00.349 --> 10:02.393
What made him get so worked up?

10:04.270 --> 10:05.855
Did he argue with Ko Jong-seok?

10:14.822 --> 10:15.740
BACKGROUND CHECK REPORT

10:15.823 --> 10:16.991
CRIMINAL RECORDS CHECK REPORT

10:17.074 --> 10:18.534
CHARGE:
COPYRIGHT INFRINGEMENT

10:20.995 --> 10:22.997
NOT GUILTY
COUNTERSUED FOR FALSE ACCUSATION

10:26.751 --> 10:29.003
FAMOUS SONGWRITER KO JONG-SEOK
SUED FOR COPYRIGHT INFRINGEMENT…

10:29.086 --> 10:30.254
"Copyright infringement"?

10:32.131 --> 10:34.967
Something smells fishy for sure.

10:36.844 --> 10:39.055
But he's a really nice guy.

10:39.930 --> 10:42.767
He cooked for us trainees at his house.

10:43.351 --> 10:45.645
He gave us private lessons too.

10:46.354 --> 10:48.397
Is your phone an Android?

10:49.273 --> 10:50.107
Yes.

10:50.858 --> 10:53.611
Give me your account ID and password.

10:54.612 --> 10:56.989
The ID is "cheerupsu-a."

10:57.573 --> 10:59.450
"Cheer up, Su-a."

10:59.533 --> 11:02.787
The password is "grandma0314."

11:05.915 --> 11:07.041
Let's see.

11:07.124 --> 11:08.292
What are you trying to do?

11:08.376 --> 11:10.878
If her phone is connected
to this web portal,

11:10.961 --> 11:12.922
it can be tracked
even if it's out of service.

11:13.506 --> 11:16.467
But I doubt the culprit has Su-a's phone.

11:16.550 --> 11:19.637
It's possible if something important
is saved on her phone.

11:20.638 --> 11:23.015
You said you visited his house, right?

11:23.516 --> 11:24.475
Where is that?

11:26.685 --> 11:28.813
It's near Riverland.

11:29.772 --> 11:30.606
Wait.

11:31.440 --> 11:32.566
KIM SU-A'S PHONE

11:36.278 --> 11:37.780
No way.

11:38.489 --> 11:40.825
RIVERLAND

11:47.581 --> 11:49.166
<i>Should we report it to the police?</i>

11:50.000 --> 11:52.211
Not yet. We need to gather more evidence.

11:52.294 --> 11:53.379
How?

11:53.462 --> 11:56.674
I better look more into Ko Jong-seok.

12:01.971 --> 12:03.055
Do you know

12:04.181 --> 12:06.851
what tamed the wolf to be like the dog?

12:07.768 --> 12:08.602
Pardon?

12:09.186 --> 12:10.062
A chunk of meat.

12:12.314 --> 12:16.444
A chunk of meat thrown to a wolf
that was cast out from the group.

12:21.991 --> 12:25.119
After getting a taste of meat
without having to make an effort,

12:25.202 --> 12:27.413
the wolf became a loyal dog.

12:28.289 --> 12:29.540
Now,

12:30.124 --> 12:33.252
what will happen if it only takes the meat
and doesn't show its loyalty?

12:34.378 --> 12:36.672
Let's say it even bites the giving hand.

12:38.424 --> 12:40.134
What should be done to that dog?

12:42.052 --> 12:43.471
Yes, I'm listening.

12:43.971 --> 12:46.682
Would you take in that bastard
if it were you?

12:47.600 --> 12:49.477
P-Please show mercy.

12:53.689 --> 12:54.940
Memorize this.

12:55.024 --> 12:56.609
It's your script in court.

13:02.072 --> 13:03.782
You'll be released before you turn 70.

13:04.617 --> 13:06.410
It's because of that damn attorney!

13:07.786 --> 13:08.913
That punk

13:09.872 --> 13:12.583
was unhinged. I'm telling you.

13:12.666 --> 13:16.086
Everyone is unhinged in this crazy world.

13:17.338 --> 13:18.380
It was Lee Gang-pung.

13:20.341 --> 13:22.176
My underling back in the Oseong Gang,

13:23.052 --> 13:24.428
Lee Gang-pung.

13:25.971 --> 13:26.805
Who?

13:28.349 --> 13:29.391
I know…

13:29.975 --> 13:31.685
it sounds ridiculous and crazy.

13:31.769 --> 13:32.645
The name.

13:33.646 --> 13:34.522
What's the name again?

13:35.105 --> 13:36.065
Lee Gang-pung.

13:37.983 --> 13:39.151
Lee Gang-pung.

13:41.195 --> 13:43.656
The truth is, Lee Gang-pung was…

13:45.199 --> 13:46.617
a gangster.

13:47.493 --> 13:48.410
Keep talking.

13:50.162 --> 13:52.498
That damn attorney was a weakling

13:53.290 --> 13:55.417
until his eyes suddenly changed.

13:55.501 --> 13:56.460
Who are you?

13:57.670 --> 13:58.796
Me?

14:00.172 --> 14:03.175
I'm gangster attorney, Lee Gang-pung!

14:04.635 --> 14:06.387
It made no sense at all.

14:07.346 --> 14:08.639
It turns out that punk--

14:08.722 --> 14:12.268
He died…
while getting surgery for his snoring.

14:21.360 --> 14:22.987
Keep your mouth shut until I come back.

14:39.336 --> 14:41.547
Look more into Shin I-rang Law Office.

14:41.630 --> 14:44.258
Everything including its location,
employees, and clients.

14:44.925 --> 14:45.843
Yes, sir.

14:47.761 --> 14:52.308
MR. KIM'S REAL ESTATE OFFICE

14:54.310 --> 14:57.605
- Hello.
- Welcome.

14:58.188 --> 14:59.356
Well…

15:00.357 --> 15:03.193
I'd like to get in touch
with the male shaman,

15:03.277 --> 15:05.863
the former tenant
of Okcheon Building's Unit 501.

15:07.197 --> 15:10.200
Why would a priest want to reach a shaman?

15:11.368 --> 15:12.703
Beats me.

15:12.786 --> 15:14.788
Things just turned out that way.

15:14.872 --> 15:16.290
Have a seat.

15:19.084 --> 15:21.086
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

15:22.755 --> 15:25.424
Can you go check
if Ko Jong-seok is inside?

15:26.050 --> 15:27.051
Okay.

15:27.134 --> 15:28.928
But…

15:30.387 --> 15:32.514
Well, good luck then.

15:32.598 --> 15:33.557
You can do it.

15:34.183 --> 15:35.351
She left already.

15:36.894 --> 15:38.395
How fast.

15:39.396 --> 15:40.397
Good luck to us too.

15:45.861 --> 15:47.404
What's taking her so long?

15:47.488 --> 15:49.114
What if something happened?

16:11.804 --> 16:13.514
This won't do. I'm going inside for a bit.

16:13.597 --> 16:15.724
Wait, let me go with you.

16:15.808 --> 16:17.851
One of us has to stay here just in case.

16:17.935 --> 16:19.520
I'll call you if something happens.

16:19.603 --> 16:22.606
Then, take this at least.

16:22.690 --> 16:24.024
What is it?

16:24.108 --> 16:25.317
I bought it online.

16:26.110 --> 16:28.028
W-Why do you carry this with you?

16:28.112 --> 16:31.365
I bought it for Sa-rang.
It's a frightening world, you know.

16:35.744 --> 16:36.662
Whoa, man!

16:37.788 --> 16:39.164
Sorry.

17:32.718 --> 17:34.803
You shouldn't be spacing out here.

17:34.887 --> 17:36.472
- Let's get out for now.
- <i>You're a flower</i>

17:37.598 --> 17:41.518
<i>With a scent that has yet</i>

17:42.644 --> 17:43.812
- What are you doing?
- <i>To bloom</i>

17:45.314 --> 17:46.648
- It's my song.
- <i>You're a flower</i>

17:47.316 --> 17:48.233
What?

17:48.317 --> 17:52.529
- I wrote that song and even its lyrics.
- <i>With many dreams that have yet</i>

17:53.655 --> 17:54.907
<i>To be dreamt</i>

17:55.866 --> 18:00.954
<i>- I want you to dazzle like a day in spring</i>
<i>- I want you to dazzle like a day in spring</i>

18:01.038 --> 18:06.335
<i>- I want you to hold the blue sky</i>
<i>- I want you to hold the blue sky</i>

18:07.419 --> 18:08.962
I wrote this song

18:09.046 --> 18:12.633
in hopes for people to feel happy
when they listen to my music.

18:17.054 --> 18:18.889
GLORY ENTERTAINMENT
LOANNE

18:20.140 --> 18:22.518
<i>I'd work part-time at night</i>
<i>after practicing all day.</i>

18:22.601 --> 18:23.727
<i>I thought it was unfair.</i>

18:24.728 --> 18:25.854
BEAUTIFUL FLOWER

18:25.938 --> 18:28.148
<i>I wasn't like other trainees.</i>

18:28.232 --> 18:32.111
<i>I didn't have what they naturally had.</i>

18:34.279 --> 18:37.366
<i>But I didn't want</i>
<i>to waste time complaining.</i>

18:38.367 --> 18:41.662
<i>Even though I was born poor,</i>
<i>I believed I could change my life.</i>

18:42.996 --> 18:44.540
<i>I was going to live differently.</i>

18:45.791 --> 18:48.919
This is why he killed you.

18:50.587 --> 18:52.589
And why your phone was gone from the roof.

18:54.466 --> 18:55.968
But how did he know?

18:56.552 --> 18:58.971
People don't know
that my songs are saved on my phone.

19:06.395 --> 19:08.147
Songwriting is a piece of cake.

19:08.230 --> 19:10.315
Which song should be next?

19:15.988 --> 19:16.905
My phone.

19:19.032 --> 19:20.909
That piece of trash.

19:21.785 --> 19:24.955
He deserves a taste of burning hell.

19:28.584 --> 19:29.960
What the heck?

19:39.303 --> 19:40.137
Hey.

19:40.721 --> 19:43.098
Did you know that there are
others who know that Su-a wrote songs?

19:43.891 --> 19:44.808
And you didn't…

19:45.726 --> 19:47.603
I better meet with her first.

19:47.686 --> 19:50.397
Who is he talking about?

19:51.106 --> 19:52.316
Emma.

19:52.399 --> 19:54.860
<i>It talks to me</i>
<i>I used to tremble all night long</i>

19:54.943 --> 19:57.029
<i>But I'm going to be a star now</i>

19:57.112 --> 19:57.988
The end!

19:58.071 --> 20:00.657
Are you for real!

20:00.741 --> 20:02.868
How do you write such lyrics?

20:02.951 --> 20:05.412
Stop. You're making me embarrassed.

20:05.495 --> 20:08.373
Emma, you have to keep this
from everyone else, okay?

20:08.957 --> 20:10.083
I'll give it some thought.

20:10.584 --> 20:13.921
You know what?
I'm suddenly craving some milk tea.

20:14.713 --> 20:16.632
Oh, come on!

20:16.715 --> 20:18.508
Don't tell anyone!

20:18.592 --> 20:20.510
Emma knows almost all my songs.

20:21.678 --> 20:22.638
Of course!

20:23.222 --> 20:26.683
I can't use any of Su-a's songs
if someone else knows about them.

20:26.767 --> 20:28.769
Who is he talking to?

20:28.852 --> 20:31.688
It's someone who knows you and Emma
and that you wrote songs.

20:35.359 --> 20:36.985
It's probably Abel.

20:37.569 --> 20:39.488
Three, four, five--

20:39.571 --> 20:40.530
Hey!

20:41.114 --> 20:42.366
Move to the left.

20:42.449 --> 20:45.494
To the left, not to the right! Must I keep
repeating myself? Are you an idiot?

20:47.746 --> 20:49.331
I'm sick and tired of this.

20:49.915 --> 20:51.250
You piss me off.

20:57.923 --> 21:00.676
<i>I often got mad at Abel</i>
<i>because she kept making mistakes.</i>

21:01.260 --> 21:02.594
She probably hated my guts.

21:03.178 --> 21:04.554
Does she know about your songs too?

21:04.638 --> 21:06.390
EVERYWHERE YOUR FOOTSTEP TOUCHES

21:09.309 --> 21:10.936
<i>She saw me write songs.</i>

21:11.603 --> 21:13.188
<i>She must've told Mr. Ko about it.</i>

21:15.315 --> 21:18.443
Ask her to meet up immediately.
I'll be there too.

21:20.904 --> 21:21.905
She's in danger.

21:21.989 --> 21:23.156
- Let's hurry after him.
- Okay.

21:27.119 --> 21:28.287
Who is it?

21:28.370 --> 21:29.871
<i>I'm Attorney Han Na-hyun.</i>

21:30.580 --> 21:32.416
- An attorney?
- Attorney Han?

21:32.499 --> 21:34.835
<i>I'm from Taebaek Law Firm,</i>
<i>which recently signed</i>

21:34.918 --> 21:37.045
<i>a partnership with Glory Entertainment.</i>

21:39.589 --> 21:40.590
Wait a moment, please.

21:45.679 --> 21:47.347
- Hello.
- Hi.

21:49.349 --> 21:50.892
- Are you alone?
- Yes.

21:50.976 --> 21:53.312
What brings you all the way here?

21:54.521 --> 21:57.399
Do you remember the man
who barged into the company yesterday?

21:57.983 --> 21:59.651
Yes, what about that wacko?

21:59.735 --> 22:02.195
He assaulted a guard.

22:02.279 --> 22:05.949
The CEO asked me to secure his information
in case of future trouble.

22:06.033 --> 22:07.034
And?

22:07.617 --> 22:10.871
I checked the footage
and saw you two talk.

22:10.954 --> 22:12.539
Did you notice anything strange?

22:12.622 --> 22:14.583
Yes, I did.

22:14.666 --> 22:15.751
He acted like Loanne.

22:16.543 --> 22:18.295
He was totally into her.

22:18.879 --> 22:20.714
You mean, the trainee who died of a fall?

22:20.797 --> 22:21.798
Yes.

22:21.882 --> 22:24.885
It happens. Perverted wackos
that approach us acting like they're fans.

22:24.968 --> 22:26.595
That little…

22:28.180 --> 22:29.514
Perverted wacko…

22:30.223 --> 22:32.893
How dare he humiliate that poor girl
who committed suicide.

22:34.436 --> 22:37.105
You were in the building
the day Loanne died.

22:38.106 --> 22:39.483
Did you perhaps meet her?

22:39.566 --> 22:42.110
No. I didn't even see her that day.

22:42.778 --> 22:43.695
Is that right?

22:44.321 --> 22:49.326
Then, I guess you're clueless
about why she made her choice.

22:49.910 --> 22:50.952
Hold on.

22:51.703 --> 22:53.538
Why are you suddenly asking me this?

22:54.289 --> 22:56.208
Aren't you after that perverted wacko?

22:56.833 --> 22:57.793
I am.

22:58.376 --> 22:59.878
I apologize if it offended you.

22:59.961 --> 23:01.922
I'm busy right now.

23:02.005 --> 23:03.381
Please leave.

23:04.341 --> 23:05.801
Thank you for your cooperation.

23:24.736 --> 23:25.987
- Yeah?
- Bong-su.

23:26.071 --> 23:27.114
Ko Jong-seok left home.

23:27.197 --> 23:29.491
Please follow him and keep me updated.

23:29.574 --> 23:31.827
- Is it Ko Jong-seok?
- Oh, my goodness.

23:32.536 --> 23:34.788
Is he your favorite artist?

23:35.705 --> 23:37.290
How did you know I was here?

23:38.416 --> 23:40.043
It was hard not to know.

23:44.798 --> 23:46.675
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

23:49.803 --> 23:51.513
Anyway, why were you in the house?

23:52.347 --> 23:54.599
It's a long story.

23:54.683 --> 23:55.851
I'm a bit busy right now.

23:56.726 --> 23:58.812
You still have to explain.

23:58.895 --> 24:00.522
Or I'll report you for trespassing.

24:03.316 --> 24:07.612
It's about Su-a, the girl who fell
from Glory Entertainment's rooftop.

24:11.116 --> 24:14.744
So, Ko Jong-seok killed Su-a
over her songs

24:14.828 --> 24:16.830
and he still has her phone?

24:17.455 --> 24:19.499
You have quite the imagination.

24:19.583 --> 24:21.751
It's a fact, not my imagination.

24:21.835 --> 24:23.879
I see, a fact.

24:24.713 --> 24:26.548
Then, let me fact-check something too.

24:27.632 --> 24:29.801
How did you know all these details?

24:32.053 --> 24:33.054
That's…

24:33.138 --> 24:34.639
It's not only this time.

24:34.723 --> 24:37.601
You knew that the hard disk was
with Cho Gi-cheol

24:37.684 --> 24:41.354
and that Attorney Byeon
and Managing Partner Yang met in private.

24:42.147 --> 24:45.400
How did you get your hands
on such secret and private information

24:45.483 --> 24:47.110
known only to the parties involved?

24:47.194 --> 24:48.653
It's natural you'd find it strange.

24:48.737 --> 24:52.115
I'd love to tell you everything
and get it off my chest.

24:52.199 --> 24:53.909
But I have no time.

24:53.992 --> 24:57.287
I must go now, or it'll be dangerous
for the girl who knows about Su-a's songs.

24:58.663 --> 24:59.873
Who is that girl?

24:59.956 --> 25:02.209
Emma, a Glory trainee.

25:03.210 --> 25:04.127
Let's go together.

25:05.295 --> 25:07.672
Glory artists are my clients,

25:07.756 --> 25:09.799
and I'm obliged to protect my clients.

25:09.883 --> 25:13.011
Then, can you find Abel?

25:13.094 --> 25:15.388
She's another Glory trainee
involved in this case.

25:15.472 --> 25:17.641
Please stop her
from committing more crimes.

25:17.724 --> 25:18.850
I'll go to Emma.

25:18.934 --> 25:20.518
Do you even know where they are?

25:21.853 --> 25:24.856
Oh, I need you to locate them too.

25:26.274 --> 25:28.693
I'll get their locations
through the prosecution.

25:29.277 --> 25:30.946
- Thank you.
- In exchange,

25:31.655 --> 25:33.657
be honest with me after this case

25:34.574 --> 25:37.285
about who you work with
and who's helping you.

25:39.371 --> 25:40.372
Okay.

25:41.957 --> 25:43.041
By the way,

25:44.251 --> 25:45.835
could I borrow…

25:46.795 --> 25:47.712
You mean, my car?

26:10.235 --> 26:12.028
<i>Turn right ahead.</i>

26:23.748 --> 26:25.000
That's Emma's car.

26:25.083 --> 26:27.377
Thank goodness,
we arrived before Ko Jong-seok.

26:32.841 --> 26:33.842
Who is that?

27:02.787 --> 27:03.788
Attorney Shin?

27:04.414 --> 27:06.624
What are you doing here?

27:08.585 --> 27:09.794
Did you follow me?

27:09.878 --> 27:11.379
No, listen to me--

27:11.463 --> 27:12.797
Don't come close.

27:12.881 --> 27:14.174
I'll call the police.

27:14.257 --> 27:15.300
Okay.

27:15.884 --> 27:17.510
I'll talk from over here.

27:18.928 --> 27:20.096
You…

27:21.222 --> 27:23.141
were asked to come here by Abel, right?

27:23.224 --> 27:24.476
What?

27:24.559 --> 27:26.853
What are you talking about?

27:27.437 --> 27:29.606
Su-a left her self-written songs
on her phone.

27:30.190 --> 27:31.274
How did you know?

27:32.609 --> 27:34.194
I heard her phone was missing.

27:34.277 --> 27:35.445
And in her phone,

27:36.029 --> 27:38.865
there's even video of Su-a singing them.
The one you took.

27:40.075 --> 27:42.577
So, how did you--

27:42.660 --> 27:44.704
What matters more than your question

27:44.788 --> 27:49.376
is that Ko Jong-seok committed murder
for Su-a's songs and took her phone.

27:49.459 --> 27:51.711
He even saw the video you took.

27:53.463 --> 27:54.464
It can't be.

27:54.547 --> 27:57.175
He's trying to kill you too
for knowing that.

27:58.593 --> 28:00.929
He can't use Su-a's songs
as long as you know them.

28:03.973 --> 28:05.767
Mr. Ko couldn't have done such a thing.

28:05.850 --> 28:07.435
Su-a said the same.

28:08.770 --> 28:09.604
When?

28:10.605 --> 28:13.024
Were you acquainted with her
when she was alive?

28:13.983 --> 28:16.820
Well, it's too complicated to explain.

28:20.490 --> 28:21.699
Oh, no. He's here already.

28:23.034 --> 28:25.662
Here. Keep this with you.

28:26.162 --> 28:28.081
I'll try talking to him,

28:28.164 --> 28:30.959
but if he acts violently,
don't hesitate to…

28:32.043 --> 28:32.877
Okay?

28:34.879 --> 28:35.755
Okay.

28:52.564 --> 28:54.274
Mister, watch out!

29:14.794 --> 29:16.713
What the? What's going on?

29:18.339 --> 29:20.133
Wait. This punk…

29:20.216 --> 29:22.635
Why? Do you know him?

29:22.719 --> 29:24.304
He's a wacko Loanne fan.

29:25.221 --> 29:26.306
Why is he sprawled out here?

29:26.389 --> 29:28.433
I took care of him.

29:28.516 --> 29:31.978
He knows that you were with Loanne
on the day she died.

29:32.061 --> 29:33.646
What are you talking about?

29:33.730 --> 29:35.106
No one else was there except us.

29:35.190 --> 29:36.566
Exactly!

29:36.649 --> 29:38.401
I don't know how,

29:38.485 --> 29:41.488
but he even knows
about the songs saved on that cow's phone.

29:42.071 --> 29:44.032
We have to act quickly. Where's the phone?

29:48.578 --> 29:49.788
Here.

29:50.663 --> 29:51.956
Found it.

29:52.040 --> 29:54.334
With fingerprints as perfect evidence.

29:54.417 --> 29:56.211
Give it back to me now.

29:58.838 --> 29:59.839
But I definitely…

30:00.423 --> 30:02.759
I expected it
and removed the battery in advance.

30:03.426 --> 30:04.677
You expected it?

30:06.888 --> 30:07.847
Oh, one more thing.

30:07.931 --> 30:11.351
Can you go to Glory Entertainment
and find me the Tomorrow Idol scorecard?

30:11.684 --> 30:12.811
ATTORNEY HAN NA-HYUN

30:16.689 --> 30:17.941
ROUND 9 SCORECARD

30:20.151 --> 30:23.029
2ND LOANNE
8TH EMMA

30:23.613 --> 30:24.864
I get it now.

30:25.949 --> 30:26.783
What?

30:26.866 --> 30:29.786
With only the final round left,

30:29.869 --> 30:31.996
you were ranked second
while Emma was ranked eighth

30:32.080 --> 30:33.665
and Abel was ranked 12th.

30:34.707 --> 30:38.169
According to the rules,
only the top seven can debut.

30:38.253 --> 30:41.798
Emma can be part of the group
only if one of the top seven is gone.

30:42.382 --> 30:44.717
And Abel was not likely to debut at all.

30:46.219 --> 30:47.220
So?

30:47.804 --> 30:49.681
In most cases, the culprit is…

30:52.100 --> 30:53.601
whoever benefits the most.

30:58.898 --> 31:01.776
And that's Emma in this case.

31:10.785 --> 31:13.037
Geez. I hoped otherwise,

31:13.121 --> 31:15.290
but a bad hunch always hits the mark.

31:16.875 --> 31:17.959
Ko Jong-seok!

31:22.088 --> 31:23.339
See?

31:23.423 --> 31:25.425
It's way too obvious.

31:28.761 --> 31:30.471
What do we do now, I-rang?

31:30.555 --> 31:32.515
Ko Jong-seok will come to where I will be.

31:32.599 --> 31:34.350
I want you to wait nearby

31:34.434 --> 31:36.811
and get him when he runs away from me.

31:36.895 --> 31:39.772
Y-You want me to get him?

31:39.856 --> 31:41.691
You must've played a detective role.

31:42.233 --> 31:43.651
You know the Miranda warning, right?

31:45.528 --> 31:46.487
Who are you?

31:47.155 --> 31:49.657
Detective Yoon Bong-su
from Gangnam PD's Violent Crimes Unit 1.

31:49.741 --> 31:52.452
You're under arrest for
aggravated robbery and gangster murder.

31:52.535 --> 31:54.954
You have the right to consult silence.

31:55.038 --> 31:58.750
And you have the right
to remain an attorney.

31:58.833 --> 31:59.792
Don't move.

32:07.675 --> 32:09.594
Mister, hurry up!

32:12.722 --> 32:13.681
Don't move!

32:23.358 --> 32:25.276
Running away won't do.

32:26.277 --> 32:28.196
Who are you to lecture me?

32:28.863 --> 32:29.739
Me?

32:30.323 --> 32:31.741
I told you. I'm Su-a's attorney.

32:33.701 --> 32:36.162
She doesn't have an attorney. She's dead!

32:36.245 --> 32:39.958
A dead person also needs an attorney
if they died a wrongful death.

32:40.708 --> 32:43.628
Let's go get you punished
for what you did.

32:45.838 --> 32:47.298
Mister, wait.

32:49.133 --> 32:51.427
Can you ask her why she did it?

32:51.511 --> 32:52.887
It's useless now.

32:56.432 --> 32:58.059
We were friends.

32:59.268 --> 33:01.062
I want to know why she did it.

33:03.940 --> 33:06.317
Okay, I'll ask her.

33:07.694 --> 33:09.195
What's with him? He's scaring me.

33:09.779 --> 33:12.991
Su-a wants to know why you killed her.

33:15.368 --> 33:17.245
You really are nuts, aren't you?

33:17.328 --> 33:19.080
You were friends once.

33:20.331 --> 33:21.416
Why did you kill your friend?

33:21.499 --> 33:22.542
Friend?

33:23.918 --> 33:24.877
Bullshit.

33:26.379 --> 33:30.341
Not once have I considered Su-a a friend.

33:31.718 --> 33:34.095
You make friends with those at your level.

33:35.972 --> 33:38.141
Do you think she was at my level?

33:47.817 --> 33:50.778
<i>I took all kinds of lessons</i>
<i>thanks to my parents' support.</i>

33:50.862 --> 33:52.697
<i>And I always got satisfying results.</i>

33:53.322 --> 33:54.657
<i>I was so happy</i>

33:55.533 --> 33:57.326
<i>until Su-a joined the agency.</i>

33:57.410 --> 34:00.788
Hello, my name is Kim Su-a.
I hope we get along.

34:01.789 --> 34:04.959
<i>She was wearing clothes</i>
<i>that my family wouldn't even use as rags,</i>

34:05.043 --> 34:06.544
<i>but that didn't faze her.</i>

34:09.255 --> 34:10.673
I'll do my best!

34:12.050 --> 34:15.094
<i>She was rather proud</i>
<i>that she had three part-time jobs.</i>

34:15.845 --> 34:18.848
APPLE JUICE

34:26.564 --> 34:29.233
I'm sorry about earlier.

34:30.109 --> 34:33.112
I was rash and lost my temper.

34:33.821 --> 34:34.697
I'm sorry.

34:35.656 --> 34:39.118
If you're sorry,
teach me how to play the guitar.

34:40.578 --> 34:42.413
I hear it's easy to write songs
knowing chords.

34:46.292 --> 34:47.460
Okay.

34:47.543 --> 34:49.545
<i>Su-a would get worked up</i>
<i>without knowing her place,</i>

34:49.629 --> 34:51.464
<i>but strangely, the girls were fond of her.</i>

34:52.423 --> 34:54.425
<i>They easily accepted her apology.</i>

34:55.134 --> 34:57.512
<i>They understood and liked her.</i>

34:58.846 --> 34:59.889
<i>It was annoying.</i>

35:00.932 --> 35:02.391
EMMA
FINAL RANK: 7TH, B

35:02.475 --> 35:04.477
- Loanne!
- You're amazing, Loanne!

35:04.560 --> 35:05.645
1ST, 96 POINTS
LOANNE

35:05.728 --> 35:07.814
<i>Su-a was always better than me.</i>

35:08.773 --> 35:11.067
<i>She was just born</i>
<i>with what I couldn't have</i>

35:11.776 --> 35:13.444
<i>even after I gave it my all.</i>

35:14.278 --> 35:15.822
<i>It was so unfair.</i>

35:21.160 --> 35:22.620
Emma, congratulations.

35:22.703 --> 35:24.580
We'll be able to debut together.

35:25.248 --> 35:26.874
<i>I wanted to tear that mouth of hers.</i>

35:26.958 --> 35:28.167
Let's have <i>tteokbokki</i> today.

35:28.251 --> 35:30.878
I got my paycheck.
It's on me to congratulate you.

35:31.546 --> 35:32.672
- Sweet.
- What do you say?

35:32.755 --> 35:33.714
<i>You're a devil.</i>

35:34.298 --> 35:37.510
<i>A filthy devil</i>
<i>who rattles me all the time.</i>

35:38.636 --> 35:41.097
<i>It talks to me</i>
<i>I used to tremble all night long</i>

35:41.180 --> 35:43.349
<i>But I'm going to be a star now</i>

35:43.432 --> 35:44.559
The end!

35:45.184 --> 35:47.019
Are you for real!

35:48.271 --> 35:50.481
How do you write such lyrics?

35:50.565 --> 35:53.109
Emma, you have to keep this
from everyone else, okay?

35:53.734 --> 35:54.777
I'll give it some thought.

35:55.570 --> 35:57.780
BEAUTIFUL FLOWER, STAR, DON'T STOP,
STREET FULL OF SUNSHINE…

35:57.864 --> 35:59.699
Maybe you really are a genius.

36:00.658 --> 36:03.369
No, I just wrote these in my spare time.

36:05.788 --> 36:08.291
Can you send me this song?

36:09.250 --> 36:11.794
It might cheer me up
when things are tough.

36:11.878 --> 36:12.712
Okay.

36:13.880 --> 36:15.423
But don't share it with anyone else.

36:19.177 --> 36:21.762
<i>- I collected her songs one after another.</i>
- These too.

36:23.055 --> 36:24.640
You wrote all these?

36:26.392 --> 36:28.311
I wrote them in my spare time.

36:28.853 --> 36:29.937
A little childish, right?

36:30.938 --> 36:33.065
Childish? No way. They're amazing.

36:34.066 --> 36:36.402
Actually, this can be your debut song.

36:38.279 --> 36:39.572
- Really?
- Yeah!

36:39.655 --> 36:43.159
<i>From that moment, I started</i>
<i>to have more reasons to get rid of her.</i>

36:43.743 --> 36:45.953
She isn't even our leader.

36:46.037 --> 36:48.164
I can't stand watching her act up anymore.

36:48.247 --> 36:52.168
Let's tell them we'll all drop out
if she doesn't.

36:52.960 --> 36:54.837
The CEO won't be able to ignore us

36:54.921 --> 36:56.881
because of my dad's investment.

36:58.174 --> 37:01.969
<i>I threatened the girls</i>
<i>and forced Su-a out of the audition.</i>

37:03.721 --> 37:05.848
<i>Everything went as I wanted.</i>

37:10.978 --> 37:12.772
<i>I followed her up to the rooftop</i>

37:12.855 --> 37:15.066
<i>because I wanted to see her sob.</i>

37:16.692 --> 37:20.821
<i>I thought I'd feel great</i>
<i>to see her in despair.</i>

37:37.713 --> 37:39.006
Why the heck is she smiling?

37:40.091 --> 37:43.344
<i>She got removed from the audition,</i>
<i>but why is she looking happy?</i>

37:45.012 --> 37:46.097
<i>Push her off there.</i>

37:47.348 --> 37:48.182
What?

37:48.266 --> 37:49.225
<i>Push her off.</i>

37:50.142 --> 37:51.852
<i>This isn't the end of her.</i>

37:52.645 --> 37:55.314
<i>That girl will crawl back up</i>

37:55.398 --> 37:57.108
<i>and get on your nerves for sure.</i>

37:58.109 --> 38:02.321
<i>What if people find out</i>
<i>that she wrote all those songs?</i>

38:02.822 --> 38:04.031
I can't let that happen.

38:05.408 --> 38:09.537
<i>That's right. If she dies,</i>
<i>all her songs will be yours.</i>

38:11.205 --> 38:13.416
<i>Push her off and take her phone. Now!</i>

38:32.226 --> 38:33.894
- Did you just…
- No.

38:35.146 --> 38:36.022
…push Su-a?

38:36.105 --> 38:37.523
I said, no!

38:41.485 --> 38:43.571
I have to report this. You killed Su-a!

38:44.530 --> 38:45.740
Are you sure I killed her?

38:46.574 --> 38:47.658
What?

38:47.742 --> 38:49.410
Or maybe you killed her
to snatch her songs.

38:50.328 --> 38:51.787
What are you saying?

38:51.871 --> 38:54.290
Su-a is the one who wrote that debut song.

38:54.373 --> 38:55.958
You said you wrote it.

38:56.042 --> 38:57.168
Did I?

38:57.251 --> 38:58.586
I don't remember.

38:59.503 --> 39:00.588
Report me.

39:00.671 --> 39:03.090
Then, I'll tell them you stole her song.

39:04.425 --> 39:05.843
You think I won't do anything about it?

39:05.926 --> 39:08.387
Go ahead, do whatever you can!

39:09.472 --> 39:11.807
I doubt the police will believe you

39:12.433 --> 39:15.102
with all those suspicions
of copyright infringement.

39:24.195 --> 39:27.948
Su-a trusted Mr. Ko.

39:30.910 --> 39:33.204
But he… Su-a…

39:43.672 --> 39:44.590
What do you think?

39:47.218 --> 39:48.469
You've lost your mind.

39:56.018 --> 39:59.230
A lot of her songs
are saved on this phone.

40:00.648 --> 40:03.943
You can't even write songs
without plagiarizing.

40:06.737 --> 40:08.114
With this,

40:09.115 --> 40:11.409
you and I don't have anything to fear.

40:15.996 --> 40:16.997
How could you…

40:19.708 --> 40:21.335
How could you do that?

40:23.796 --> 40:25.798
I thought we were friends.

40:28.843 --> 40:30.052
What's wrong with you?

40:30.678 --> 40:31.679
Are you crazy?

40:33.848 --> 40:35.516
Is it my fault for being poor?

40:36.892 --> 40:39.353
Is it my fault for doing
all that I can for myself?

40:39.437 --> 40:40.980
Get back, you lunatic.

40:42.356 --> 40:43.774
Shut your damn mouth!

40:43.858 --> 40:46.694
I was excited
at the thought of debuting with you.

40:48.070 --> 40:50.322
I was so happy that it felt like a dream.

40:50.906 --> 40:53.117
What are you saying, psycho?

40:56.412 --> 40:58.622
Who the hell are you?

40:59.081 --> 40:59.915
Me?

41:00.541 --> 41:01.917
Your agency's attorney.

41:04.336 --> 41:05.796
My agency's attorney?

41:06.505 --> 41:07.590
Don't be glad.

41:08.382 --> 41:10.259
I have no intention of helping a murderer.

41:10.968 --> 41:13.095
Who are you calling a murderer?

41:16.557 --> 41:18.476
Ko Jong-seok confessed it all.

41:18.559 --> 41:20.144
And we got Su-a's phone too.

41:20.811 --> 41:22.229
You won't get away this time.

41:25.608 --> 41:27.568
What are you doing? Get up.

41:32.865 --> 41:33.741
Are you crying?

41:34.658 --> 41:36.327
Who's crying?

41:56.347 --> 42:00.226
You got many texts mourning you.

42:02.269 --> 42:03.312
It was Abel.

42:04.104 --> 42:04.939
What was?

42:06.649 --> 42:08.526
She knew that you were writing songs.

42:11.403 --> 42:12.446
<i>Dear Su-a.</i>

42:13.822 --> 42:14.657
<i>Su-a,</i>

42:15.241 --> 42:18.702
<i>I loved the songs you wrote</i>

42:19.370 --> 42:23.415
<i>because I could always feel</i>
<i>warmth and hope from your songs.</i>

42:24.667 --> 42:28.796
I didn't know she was feeling this way.

42:29.672 --> 42:33.467
Sincerity is bound to reach someone.

42:35.719 --> 42:38.639
Now, should we find your mom's number?

42:41.267 --> 42:43.227
I guess it's the one from your last call.

42:44.311 --> 42:45.312
Right.

42:45.396 --> 42:48.232
CALL HISTORY
MOM

42:48.315 --> 42:49.400
Here it is.

42:53.988 --> 42:55.155
MOM

42:55.239 --> 42:57.491
Mister, wait.

42:58.033 --> 42:58.867
What is it?

43:00.077 --> 43:04.290
Do you think
she should be informed that I'm dead?

43:05.374 --> 43:07.209
Don't you want to see her?

43:08.294 --> 43:09.837
I do, but…

43:15.301 --> 43:16.719
How about this, then?

43:16.802 --> 43:20.431
I'll use this number
to find where your mom is.

43:21.015 --> 43:24.310
Then you can just look at her from afar.

43:25.978 --> 43:27.146
Okay.

43:32.276 --> 43:34.612
HOSEONG SEOUL HOSPITAL

43:38.782 --> 43:39.783
All right.

43:41.201 --> 43:42.911
Things aren't looking good.

43:43.621 --> 43:44.913
I see.

43:44.997 --> 43:47.625
You have a month at the longest
until you go completely blind.

43:47.708 --> 43:49.293
It's not enough time to find a donor.

43:50.502 --> 43:51.545
Right.

43:51.629 --> 43:54.923
Oh, did you meet the person
you wanted to meet?

43:58.177 --> 43:59.178
Not yet.

44:00.012 --> 44:01.388
You need to hurry.

44:02.389 --> 44:04.391
Your sight will get worse and worse.

44:05.643 --> 44:06.477
Okay.

44:21.367 --> 44:22.534
Mom…

44:33.629 --> 44:35.506
Her medical record says

44:36.131 --> 44:40.594
that she was diagnosed
with viral keratitis 18 years ago.

44:43.472 --> 44:45.808
Eighteen years ago?

44:46.850 --> 44:48.519
That's when I was one.

44:50.646 --> 44:51.814
BABY FORMULA

45:00.948 --> 45:02.241
Ow!

45:02.324 --> 45:03.742
Su-a, are you okay?

45:04.743 --> 45:05.744
Oh, no.

45:05.828 --> 45:07.746
- I'm so sorry.
<i>- She sent me to Grandma…</i>

45:07.830 --> 45:08.789
Su-a.

45:08.872 --> 45:10.999
<i>…to protect me.</i>

45:11.083 --> 45:12.418
GLORY'S NEW FACE, TRAINEE KIM SU-A

45:12.501 --> 45:14.169
MY SU-A IS THE BEST

45:20.717 --> 45:22.469
MY SU-A

45:28.725 --> 45:30.227
Su-a?

45:32.896 --> 45:33.981
It's Mom.

45:39.570 --> 45:40.779
My dear Su-a,

45:42.406 --> 45:44.575
you grew up to be such a pretty girl.

45:46.660 --> 45:47.828
Thank you.

45:50.914 --> 45:51.957
Su-a.

45:53.625 --> 45:54.835
Will you…

45:55.836 --> 45:57.713
meet me just once?

45:59.715 --> 46:01.091
The reason she called was…

46:06.763 --> 46:10.058
because she wanted to see me
one last time before she lost her sight.

46:21.153 --> 46:21.987
Mister.

46:23.614 --> 46:24.740
Yes?

46:29.995 --> 46:32.623
I have one last favor to ask of you.

46:34.249 --> 46:35.667
Will you do it for me?

46:38.253 --> 46:39.254
Name anything.

46:40.589 --> 46:42.174
I'm…

46:42.257 --> 46:43.759
your attorney.

46:54.520 --> 46:58.148
Kim Su-a registered herself
as an organ donor when she was alive.

46:58.232 --> 47:02.194
And after her death,
four precious lives were saved.

47:03.237 --> 47:05.697
Our organization is keeping her corneas.

47:06.490 --> 47:08.617
Family donation is perfectly legal.

47:09.535 --> 47:12.204
I see. Thank you.

47:14.456 --> 47:16.124
<i>I want to</i>…

47:17.709 --> 47:19.378
give my eyes to my mom.

47:25.676 --> 47:27.469
I got them from her.

47:29.304 --> 47:32.099
It's only right
that I give them back to her.

47:57.124 --> 48:00.085
Now, try to open your eyes slowly.

48:09.094 --> 48:10.095
Mom.

48:10.178 --> 48:12.848
Yes, can you see me?

48:15.601 --> 48:16.560
I can.

48:18.478 --> 48:19.479
I…

48:22.608 --> 48:24.276
I see you so clearly.

48:27.362 --> 48:29.323
What do I do?

48:30.616 --> 48:34.870
I feel so bad for our Su-a.
I don't know what to do, Mom.

48:38.999 --> 48:41.835
Live your life to the fullest.

48:43.128 --> 48:44.504
For Su-a. That will do.

48:53.138 --> 48:54.973
I will.

48:55.057 --> 48:56.099
Good.

48:56.183 --> 48:57.809
To the fullest,

48:58.977 --> 49:02.689
I'll live a happy life for sure.

49:02.773 --> 49:03.732
Good.

49:05.108 --> 49:06.026
That will do.

49:07.778 --> 49:08.987
My precious daughter.

49:09.071 --> 49:12.115
- Mom.
- I'm proud of you, my daughter.

49:14.826 --> 49:16.286
Thanks to you,

49:17.913 --> 49:20.082
I can rest in peace now.

49:25.170 --> 49:26.421
There's no need to rush.

49:28.924 --> 49:31.760
You can stay with your mom and grandma

49:32.386 --> 49:34.054
and take your time to pass on.

49:41.603 --> 49:42.688
It's okay.

49:44.523 --> 49:46.108
This is enough already.

49:46.692 --> 49:47.818
My daughter.

49:50.404 --> 49:52.447
Thank you, Su-a.

49:54.700 --> 49:55.742
Now,

49:57.452 --> 49:59.746
my mom will protect Grandma,

50:01.206 --> 50:03.959
and Grandma will protect Mom.

50:13.677 --> 50:15.053
I'm ready to pass on.

50:40.078 --> 50:41.580
The shaman wasn't home.

50:42.372 --> 50:44.082
I asked the neighbors,

50:44.166 --> 50:46.460
and they said they didn't see him lately.

50:47.252 --> 50:50.714
It might take a little longer.

50:53.383 --> 50:54.509
He'll be okay

50:55.761 --> 50:58.472
since your son is not alone.

50:59.181 --> 51:01.433
"…for his outstanding performance."

51:01.516 --> 51:02.934
"Presented by Yoon Da-bong."

51:03.018 --> 51:04.144
Here you go.

51:04.227 --> 51:05.479
Thank you.

51:05.562 --> 51:07.063
Congratulations.

51:07.147 --> 51:09.149
- Thank you, Mother.
- Congrats, Bong-su.

51:09.232 --> 51:11.151
It wasn't me alone.

51:11.234 --> 51:13.028
<i>He has his beloved family.</i>

51:13.904 --> 51:17.157
<i>And he seems to have gotten someone</i>
<i>he can open up to.</i>

51:19.117 --> 51:22.579
Thanks to you, Su-a's case was resolved.

51:23.163 --> 51:24.456
Thank you so much.

51:25.040 --> 51:26.875
You should rather be sorry.

51:27.584 --> 51:30.086
Because of you,
I had to report my own client.

51:31.671 --> 51:32.631
Oh.

51:33.298 --> 51:34.216
I'm sorry.

51:34.800 --> 51:35.759
Well,

51:35.842 --> 51:38.804
it didn't seem intentional,
so forget the apology.

51:38.887 --> 51:39.888
Now, tell me.

51:40.472 --> 51:43.767
You promised you'd tell me
who you worked with after the case.

51:46.770 --> 51:49.231
It's not hard to tell you,

51:49.981 --> 51:52.234
but I'm afraid you won't believe it.

51:52.317 --> 51:55.237
I've been through
countless unbelievable cases.

51:55.821 --> 51:57.072
So don't worry.

51:57.781 --> 52:00.617
This one is completely different, though.

52:10.001 --> 52:10.961
Ghosts.

52:13.088 --> 52:13.922
What?

52:14.005 --> 52:16.550
I can see and communicate
with dead people.

52:17.217 --> 52:18.510
This time, it was Su-a.

52:18.593 --> 52:21.096
Last time, Lee Gang-pung's spirit told me.

52:21.179 --> 52:22.180
So…

52:22.264 --> 52:24.015
Easily put,

52:24.099 --> 52:27.102
spirits of dead people
tell me their resentful stories--

52:27.185 --> 52:28.019
Enough.

52:29.229 --> 52:33.066
And my office used to be
a shaman's house--

52:33.149 --> 52:35.110
I said, enough.

52:36.236 --> 52:37.112
Okay.

52:37.779 --> 52:38.947
Let's stop here.

52:39.656 --> 52:41.783
It's a waste of time
dealing with you anymore.

52:50.333 --> 52:52.127
This is why I was reluctant to tell you.

52:52.210 --> 52:53.712
You're the one who urged me.

52:56.006 --> 52:59.175
Actually, it's better not to believe me.

53:02.554 --> 53:03.889
Oh, I'm late.

53:05.348 --> 53:07.350
LOANNE,
I'LL REMEMBER YOU FOREVER

53:10.353 --> 53:12.022
WE LOVE YOU, LOANNE

53:12.105 --> 53:14.107
LOANNE IS MY WORLD, MY LIGHT

53:28.872 --> 53:30.874
WE'LL BE WITH YOU UNTIL THE END

53:41.259 --> 53:42.761
<i>You're a flower</i>

53:44.220 --> 53:47.474
<i>With a scent that has yet</i>

53:47.557 --> 53:48.892
I WANT YOU TO HOLD THE BLUE SKY

53:49.559 --> 53:50.977
<i>To bloom</i>

53:52.103 --> 53:53.605
<i>You're a flower</i>

53:54.814 --> 53:58.652
<i>With many dreams that have yet</i>

54:00.236 --> 54:01.696
<i>To be dreamt</i>

54:02.906 --> 54:07.243
<i>I want you to dazzle like a day in spring</i>

54:08.370 --> 54:12.707
<i>I want you to hold the blue sky</i>

54:13.708 --> 54:18.546
<i>How beautiful you will look</i>

54:19.047 --> 54:23.718
<i>How splendid your tomorrow will be</i>

54:24.386 --> 54:28.640
<i>I know</i>

54:29.933 --> 54:31.267
<i>I know it all…</i>

54:31.351 --> 54:33.061
THANK YOU FOR YOUR WARM COMFORT
I LOVE YOU

54:33.144 --> 54:34.396
YOU'RE ALIVE
AS LONG AS WE REMEMBER YOU

54:34.479 --> 54:35.730
I HOPE YOU DANCE WITH ANGELS NOW

54:35.814 --> 54:36.982
LOANNE!
I MISS YOU!

54:37.065 --> 54:38.274
WITH YOUR MUSIC
UNTIL I SEE YOU AGAIN

54:40.276 --> 54:44.698
<i>Bloom like a flower</i>

54:45.490 --> 54:48.326
<i>You're so beautiful</i>

54:48.410 --> 54:51.037
<i>In my eyes</i>

54:51.121 --> 54:55.792
<i>You have become even more beautiful</i>

54:55.875 --> 54:59.295
LET'S MEET AGAIN FOR SURE

55:01.089 --> 55:02.215
Farewell, Su-a.

55:03.675 --> 55:05.593
I'll listen to your songs every day,

55:06.511 --> 55:08.346
and I'll remember your voice.

55:08.430 --> 55:11.474
You better. I'll be watching from above.

55:16.396 --> 55:18.148
Thank you, mister.

55:19.441 --> 55:22.986
I'm sorry for causing you trouble.

55:31.911 --> 55:34.456
Su-a is looking at the two of you.

55:37.459 --> 55:38.376
Bye, Su-a.

55:38.460 --> 55:39.961
Goodbye, Su-a.

55:44.507 --> 55:45.800
Oh.

55:46.593 --> 55:48.136
I'll miss you.

55:48.720 --> 55:51.723
Be happy in heaven.

55:54.100 --> 55:55.185
Thank you.

55:55.977 --> 55:58.396
I'll miss you so much too.

55:59.022 --> 56:00.982
She says she'll miss you so much too.

56:23.088 --> 56:24.339
Goodbye.

56:26.925 --> 56:28.301
Take care.

57:41.458 --> 57:42.876
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

57:43.418 --> 57:45.462
I'M SORRY ABOUT EARLIER
AND TRY LISTENING TO THIS!

57:46.671 --> 57:47.755
He's tiresome.

57:49.799 --> 57:53.803
BEAUTIFUL FLOWER

58:11.321 --> 58:13.615
<i>Tteokbokki</i>, <i>sundae</i>,
and fish cakes. Agreed?

58:13.698 --> 58:16.784
- <i>You're a flower</i>
- And fried dumplings on top, agreed.

58:16.868 --> 58:18.536
- Agreed. Sounds great.
- Sounds great.

58:18.620 --> 58:20.330
<i>With a scent that has yet</i>

58:21.498 --> 58:23.166
<i>To bloom</i>

58:24.083 --> 58:25.543
<i>You're a flower</i>

58:27.003 --> 58:30.924
<i>With many dreams that have yet</i>

58:32.383 --> 58:33.635
<i>To be dreamt</i>

58:35.053 --> 58:39.390
<i>I want you to dazzle like a day in spring</i>

58:40.683 --> 58:45.021
<i>I want you to hold the blue sky</i>

58:45.813 --> 58:50.568
<i>- How beautiful you will look…</i>
- Sweet dreams.

58:50.652 --> 58:52.820
GOING TO A CONCERT WITH NA-HYUN!

58:52.904 --> 58:56.533
<i>How splendid your tomorrow will be</i>

58:56.616 --> 59:00.870
<i>I know</i>

59:02.038 --> 59:04.958
<i>I know it all</i>

59:05.041 --> 59:07.335
CERTIFICATE OF COMPLETION
JUDICIAL TRAINEE HAN NA-HYUN

59:07.418 --> 59:12.507
<i>Beautiful flower</i>
<i>Beautiful you…</i>

59:12.590 --> 59:14.801
THE 48TH JUDICIAL TRAINING
COMPLETION CEREMONY

59:14.884 --> 59:16.761
<i>Bloom like a flower</i>

59:18.012 --> 59:20.515
<i>You're so beautiful</i>

59:20.598 --> 59:23.059
<i>In my eyes</i>

59:23.142 --> 59:27.897
<i>You have become even more beautiful</i>

59:27.981 --> 59:33.570
- I miss you more especially today.
<i>- Beautiful flower, beautiful you</i>

59:34.153 --> 59:37.657
<i>Bloom like a flower…</i>

01:00:13.026 --> 01:00:14.235
You're here again.

01:00:17.655 --> 01:00:20.450
I handed over all the documents
related to Glory Entertainment.

01:00:22.535 --> 01:00:23.411
Noted.

01:00:33.963 --> 01:00:34.797
Here.

01:00:36.215 --> 01:00:37.300
What is it?

01:00:38.092 --> 01:00:40.261
Of all the cases that Taebaek has taken,

01:00:40.345 --> 01:00:44.474
this one is the biggest headache
in the very center of the media spotlight.

01:00:45.933 --> 01:00:47.644
Shouldn't you be reflecting on yourself?

01:00:47.727 --> 01:00:50.146
I hear the Chairman is recovering fast.

01:00:53.483 --> 01:00:55.526
That's none of your business.

01:00:55.610 --> 01:00:57.070
If we win this case,

01:00:57.153 --> 01:00:59.947
there would be nothing better
as a welcome back gift for the chairman.

01:01:00.823 --> 01:01:04.494
I'll gift wrap it with care
so that you can take the credit.

01:01:04.577 --> 01:01:05.787
A gift?

01:01:08.748 --> 01:01:10.500
- What if we lose?
- Then,

01:01:11.000 --> 01:01:13.169
you'll have a reason to kick me out.

01:01:13.836 --> 01:01:16.255
You won't suffer any losses either way.

01:01:21.719 --> 01:01:24.138
Don't let me down this time.

01:01:25.056 --> 01:01:25.932
I won't.

01:01:37.110 --> 01:01:37.944
WOMAN FOUND NOT GUILTY

01:01:38.027 --> 01:01:39.112
FOR BRUTALLY MURDERING
HER HUSBAND…

01:02:42.675 --> 01:02:43.676
Welcome.

01:02:44.635 --> 01:02:46.179
It must've been a long way coming here.

01:02:58.399 --> 01:02:59.692
Who are you?

01:03:00.693 --> 01:03:04.071
I'm your attorney, Shin I-rang.

01:03:30.973 --> 01:03:32.391
<i>Who is it this time?</i>

01:03:32.475 --> 01:03:34.310
<i>He seems to have majored in science.</i>

01:03:34.393 --> 01:03:35.853
Is the culprit your wife?

01:03:35.937 --> 01:03:39.315
<i>Are you really trying to kill me?</i>

01:03:39.398 --> 01:03:41.484
<i>You had a bright future,</i>
<i>and she killed you.</i>

01:03:41.567 --> 01:03:42.819
I'll have to meet Kim Su-jeong.

01:03:42.902 --> 01:03:45.988
<i>A place familiar enough for Kim Su-jeong</i>
<i>to abandon a body.</i>

01:03:46.072 --> 01:03:47.323
Does anywhere ring a bell?

01:03:47.406 --> 01:03:50.326
<i>He would lose his cool</i>
<i>at the sight of his own dead body.</i>

01:03:50.409 --> 01:03:52.662
<i>Wouldn't he have gone</i>
<i>to the person who killed him?</i>

01:03:52.745 --> 01:03:54.330
<i>Then, he must've gone to Kim Su-jeong.</i>

01:03:54.413 --> 01:03:55.498
<i>Why did you kill me?</i>

01:03:57.375 --> 01:04:01.337
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
